    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\nHere's the complete plan to add `next/geo` to the Next.js framework.\n\n### 5 files to create/modify\n\n| File | Action |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | **Create** — core implementation |\n| `packages/next/geo.js` | **Create** — CJS public entry (mirrors `server.js`) |\n| `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | **Create** — type declarations (mirrors `server.d.ts`) |\n| `packages/next/package.json` | **Modify** — insert `geo.js` + `geo.d.ts` in `files` array |\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | **Create** — Jest unit tests |\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- **Dual-function pattern** mirrors `userAgent()` / `userAgentFromString()`: `geo({ headers })` takes a request-like object; `geoFromHeaders(headers)` takes raw `Headers`\n- **`null` → `undefined`**: `Headers.get()` returns `null` on miss; `?? undefined` converts it cleanly for TypeScript strict mode\n- **`export type { Geo }`** in `geo.d.ts` is required by `verbatimModuleSyntax: true` in tsconfig\n- **Cloudflare fallback**: `x-vercel-ip-country` is tried first, then `cf-ipcountry`\n- **`geo.js`/`geo.d.ts` inserted after `form.d.ts`** in `package.json` (alphabetically `g` follows `f`)\n- **Haversine formula** uses Earth radius 6371 km; NY→London ≈ 5570 km ± 50 km\n- **10 built-in country codes**: US, GB, DE, FR, JP, CN, IN, BR, AU, CA\n\n### Verification sequence\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types          # fast type check (~10s)\npnpm --filter=next build          # full compile, emits dist/\npnpm test-unit                    # runs geo.test.ts\nnode -e \"console.log(Object.keys(require('./packages/next/geo.js')))\"  # smoke test\n```",
